column137: Headquartered in Barrow, AK, Arctic Slope Regional (ASRC) is a private, for profit Alaska native owned corporation representing the business interests of the Arctic Slope Inupiat. ASRC is committed to preserving the Inupiat culture and traditions which strengthen both its shareholders and the company. It represents eight villages on the north slope of Alaska which include Point Hope, Point Lay, Wainwright, Atqasuk, and Anaktuvuk Pass. The company has a growing shareholder population of 11,000, and has title to nearly five million acres of land. Its subsidiaries offer engineering and consulting services, civil construction, oil and gas support services, petroleum refining and distribution, and other services. Clients range from local to multinational corporations and local to federal governmental agencies. The company employs about 10,000 people.

column137: Established in 1983, Alaska Option Services Corporation is headquartered in Anchorage, AK. It is a provider of electronic financial transaction-related services. The company's services include ATM processing services, signature issuer processing services, PIN issuer processing services, card personalization services, and network transaction services.

Alaska Rag Company is headquartered in Fairbanks, AK. It is a supplier of handwoven mug rugs and table runners. The company offers place mats, pottery-plates, paintings, wooden boxes and vases, and handmade soaps.
Anchorage Medset Pharmacy is headquartered in Anchorage, AK. The company provides delivery-based pharmacy service. It employs about 20 people.

Established in 1972, Beaver Sports is based in Fairbanks, AK. It is a retailer of sporting goods. The company's product line includes bikes, sportswear, sunglasses and goggles, ski, and athletic products. It offers brands such as Diadora, Asics, Redline, Helly Hansen, and Red Ledge.

Founded in 1983, Carpet World of Alaska, Inc. is based in Wasilla, AK. It is a retail flooring store. The store offers products from manufacturers such as Mannington, Armstrong, Marmoleum, Konecto, and Surface Art. It offers in-home measurement, financing, and installation services.

Habitat Housewares is located in Anchorage, AK. It is a gourmet cooking and entertaining store. The store offers products such as cookware and kitchen appliances, kitchen tools, dinnerware. party accessories, and gourmet food.

Metro Home was founded in 1978 and is headquartered in Anchorage, AK. The company is a supplier of home furnishings, accessories, houseware, and gifts. Its product line includes accent tables, bedrooms, chairs, armoires, sofas, and wall units. The company features products from manufacturers such as American Leather, Bermex, Hooker, and Lazar.

Mountain View Sports Center is based in Anchorage, AK. It is a retailer of hunting gear and fishing tackle. The store's products include gun cases, binoculars, rods, gloves, tents, and accessories. Its categories include fishing, hunting, clothing, boots and shoes, camping, and books. It carry brands such as Pendleton, MSR, Leica, Fishpond, and Swarovski.

Nana Management Services, LLC. is based in Anchorage, AK. The company is a provider of support services for businesses. It services clients such as oilfields, federal, state and local governments, corporate facilities, and health care facilties.

column137: Headquartered in Barrow, AK, Arctic Slope Regional (ASRC) is a private, for profit Alaska native owned corporation representing the business interests of the Arctic Slope Inupiat. It represents eight villages on the north slope of Alaska which include Point Hope, Point Lay, Wainwright, Atqasuk, and Anaktuvuk Pass. The company has a growing shareholder population of 11,000, and has title to nearly five million acres of land. Clients range from local to multinational corporations and local to federal governmental agencies. The company employs about 10,000 people.
